President Donald J. Trump has sent a report to the Chairman (or Chairwoman) in accordance with the Elie Wiesel Genocide and Atrocities Prevention Act of 2018. The report includes a review of current efforts to prevent and respond to atrocities, a review of ongoing global atrocities, and recommendations to prevent and respond to atrocities. The report was produced in consultation with civil society, academic institutions, and other non-governmental organizations.